-- Ireland Defeats Argentina 29-9 in Rugby Test With Ferris, D'Arcy Tries
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2010-11-28T16:36:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-28/ireland-defeats-argentina-29-9-in-rugby-test-with-ferris-d-arcy-tries.html
Ireland defeated Argentina 29-9 in a
rugby union Test today in Dublin, with tries from Stephen Ferris
and Gordon D’Arcy.  Jonathan Sexton kicked 17 points, while Ronan O’Gara got a
late conversion for the hosts, who have now won seven of 12
matches against the Pumas. The win keeps Ireland seventh in the
world rankings, one spot ahead of Argentina.   Felipe Contepomi had three penalties for Argentina.  Yesterday, Dan Carter became the leading points scorer in
Test rugby as top-ranked New Zealand beat Wales 37-25 to
complete a sweep of its tour of the U.K. and Ireland.  World champion South Africa beat England 21-11, Italy
defeated Fiji 24-16, Scotland beat Samoa 19-16 and Australia
routed France 59-16.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  